
This script is designed to run an MPI job using the PBS (Portable Batch System) workload manager. It requests a single node with 12 cores and 64GB of memory. The script also specifies walltime and cputime limits for the job.

The script uses a Singularity container, `/extra/hossain/gdocker.simg`, to execute a Python script, `multiview_distance_martix.py`, with specific arguments. This script likely performs distance matrix calculations for a multiview dataset.

The script also uses PBS features to manage job output, error messages, and email notifications. It's worth noting that the email notifications are commented out in this specific example.
